&nbsp;Wash the toor dal and add 1 &frac12;&nbsp;&nbsp;cups of water to it. and keep aside.or cook along with rice as shown.
Roast the dry red chilies, fenugreek seeds, mustard seeds, whole garam masala, coriander seeds, chana dal, urad dal, fresh coconut pieces and transfer into a blender and make it into a fine powder and keep a side.&nbsp;
Heat the oil in pan and add the cumin and mustard seeds, red chilies, cashew nuts and curry leaves, after spluttering add the onions, green chilies, hing and fry till soft. Add all the chopped vegetables, turmeric powder and softly fry it.&nbsp;
Add soaked toor dal, rice, water, salt and cook it for 10 minutes.
Now add masala powder that we have prepared at earlier.Garnish the dish with coriander leaves and serve it hot.

First peel the mango skin and chop into small dices.
In a pestle, add roasted cumin seeds and crush it to a coarse powder.
Now, add chopped onion, green chillies and give it again a slight crush with&nbsp;
Then add ripe mango and muddle it again.
Season it with salt, lemon juice, chopped coriander leaves and mix well.
At last, transfer this mixture to a bowl and serve it with&nbsp;tortilla or roasted papad or fried papads.&nbsp;

In a bowl add butter in a pan and cream it.&nbsp;
In this add sugar powder, mix it well add curd, mix this and add all purpose flour, vanilla extract, mix this like a dough.
Divide the dough into equal portions. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
Make them into the round smooth balls are bullet shapes with no cracks, lightly press some pistachio on top of each ball.
Bake them into 180-degree centigrade for 15 to 18 minutes.
when you see that bottoms begin to brown lightly, remove from the oven and let it cool down, transfer to a plate.

Heat oil in a pan add chopped onions, salt saute it for few minutes, once the onions are transparent add green chilli, ginger garlic paste cook this till raw flavour is gone.
Add a pinch of turmeric powder, drumsticks and also add some water mix it and put the lid on let it cook for 5 minutes.
When drumsticks cooked add red chilli powder, coriander powder mix it and put the lid on let it cook for 2 minutes.&nbsp;
After 2 minutes add drumstick leaves cook this for few minutes.&nbsp;
When drumstick leaves soft add tomato pieces to cook this till tomatoes soft switch off the flame.Serve this with rice.

In a hot pan add red chili, peanuts, chana dal, urad dal, cumin seeds dry roast all the ingredients and make it into a powder.
Heat oil in a pan add green chili, grated beetroot, mint and coriander leaves, salt cook for 3-4 minutes then transfer this into the blender and add garlic, lemon juice makes it into a paste.Serve with chapati.
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;

Heat oil in a pan and add chopped onions, salt, curry leaves, turmeric, green chilies, ginger garlic paste, cook for 5 minutes.&nbsp;
Now add moong dal (soaked in water) cook for 2 minutes with the lid on.
Add grated beetroot cook till beetroot is tender the then add chopped spinach, mint leaves, garam masala powder, coriander powder, chilli powder saute it and add coconut mix it well.Serve with roti or rice.

In a bowl add boiled Chana dal and blend it with the hand blender or hand mash it.
In this add the seasonings pinch of salt, garam masala, chopped green chilies also you can add chat masala, chopped onions, chopped coriander and add boiled potato mix well.&nbsp;
Make it into a simple kebab and cook this on a hot tawa by adding butter, In a bowl add some shredded cabbage, onion slices, mayonnaise, tomato slices and mix well and use it as a topping.&nbsp;
once the kebab is lightly cooked and add the egg mixture on one side of the tawa to make an omelet. Once the omelet is lightly cooked place the kebab on the omelet and fold the sides of the omelet to cover it.
Now add the butter on tawa and cook the buns both sides. When it is slightly colored apply a lot of mint chutney on the buns.
Place the coat kebab on the bun and top it with the cabbage mixture. And also you can add tomato ketchup, cucumber slices and cover it with bun.And also you can add tomato ketchup, cucumber slices and cover it with bun.

Cut the paneer pieces into rectangular shape.
Take 1 tablespoon of achar into the plate and add little water mix it like a thin paste then coats the paneer pieces and keep it aside.&nbsp;
In a bowl add chickpea flour, all purpose flour, salt, ajwain, turmeric powder, chat masala, chopped coriander leaves and mix it well by adding oil.
Add some water and make first thick paste then add some more water mix it well.
Dip the coated paneer pieces into the batter and deep fry in the hot oil.
Cut into small pieces sprinkle chat masala and put on to a tooth pick and serve hot.&nbsp;

In a blender add red chilies, chopped onions, chopped ginger, curry leaves, salt, pepper corns, chana dal(soaked in the water for 4 hours) add cooking soda, make a coarse paste, transfer this into a bowl.
Then add ghee, lime juice, mix it well, make them into small dumplings and steam for 10 minutes.&nbsp;
For tempering: Heat ghee in a pan add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, red chilies, a pinch of turmeric powder, hing, curry leaves, grated coconut, salt, lemon juice, chopped coriander, sugar, add steamed vada and saut&eacute; them and switch off the flame.Serve this hot.

Soak the Masoor dal in water for 6 to 7 hours. Remove water from the whole Masoor dal and dry thick towel for 10 minutes spread out evenly so that all the water is removed.&nbsp;
Heat oil in a pan and fry the Masoor dal till the dal becomes crispy and keep it on a paper napkin to remove excess oil. And also fry cashew nuts, dry red chilly, curry leaves.&shy;&shy;&shy;&nbsp;
In a bowl add fried Masoor dal, red chilies, cashew nuts, curry leaves.&nbsp;
In this add red chili powder, dry mango powder. black salt, sev and mix it well.

Heat oil in a pan add mustard seeds when they splutter add dry red chili, cumin seeds, methi seeds, sliced onions, salt, turmeric powder, saute it.
Then add curry leaves, ginger garlic paste cook it for 2 minutes then add green chili, drumsticks and add some water, coriander powder, cumin powder, red chilli powder mix it and cook for 5 minutes.&nbsp;
Once the drumsticks are cooked add tamarind juice, jaggery, green peas and add salt to taste put the lid on and let it cook for 4 minutes. Finally, add chopped coriander.Serve with rice.
